Movement in England |edition=second |year=1983 |publisher=Counterpoint |location=London |isbn=978-0-04-301164-5 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |first=E. Ellis |last=Cashmore |year=1984 |title=The Decline of the Rastas? |journal=Religion Today |volume=1 |issue=1 |pages=3\u20134 |doi= 10.1080/13537908408580533 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |first=E. Ellis |last=Cashmore |year=1989 |title=The Dawkins Case: Official Ethnic Status for Rastas |journal=Journal of Ethnic and Migration Studies |volume=16 |number=1 |pages=158\u2013160 |doi=10.1080/1369183X.1989.9976168 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Chawane |first=Midas H. |year=2014 |title=The Rastafarian Movement in South Africa: A Religion or Way of Life? |journal=Journal for the Study of Religion |volume=27 |number=2 |pages=214\u2013237 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Chevannes |first=Barry |title=Rastafari: Roots and Ideology |url=https://archive.org/details/rastafarirootsid0000chev |url-access=registration |publisher=Syracuse University Press |location=Syracuse, New York |series=Utopianism and Communitarianism Series |year=1994 |isbn=978-0815602965 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Clarke |first=Peter B. |title=Black Paradise: The Rastafarian Movement |year=1986 |publisher=The Aquarian Press |location=Wellingborough |series=New Religious Movements Series |isbn=978-0-85030-428-2 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Edmonds |first=Ennis B. |title=Rastafari: A Very Short Introduction |year=2012 |location=Oxford |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0199584529 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Eyre |first=L. Alan |year=1985 |title=Biblical Symbolism and the Role of Fantasy Geography Among the Rastafarians of Jamaica |journal=Journal of Geography |volume=84 |issue=4 |pages=144\u2013148 |doi=10.1080/00221348508979381 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Francis |first=Wigmoore |title=Towards a Pre-History of Rastafari |year=2013 |journal=Caribbean Quarterly: A Journal of Caribbean Culture |volume=59 |i